data.description: Code Repository for `Where is Waldo (and his friends)? A comparison of anomaly detection algorithms for time-domain astronomy`

evidence: Title and citation describe a specific research study and its code: “A comparison of anomaly detection algorithms for time-domain astronomy… If you find this code useful, please cite our paper” – indicating research analysis code for that paper.

The repository is tied to a single paper and appears as code accompanying that work, suggesting it is run as an application to reproduce or explore the study’s results rather than as a reusable library.
No installation via package managers, containers, or binaries is mentioned; only the paper citation and license are given, implying distribution directly from the source repository.
